cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper is about using adversarial training for open-domain dialogue generation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses reinforcement learning (RL) to train the generative model, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new evaluation metric for dialogue generation, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound). Finally, the paper uses neural networks for dialogue generation, which could also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
